{"id":5575,"date":"2023-03-06T16:52:17","date_gmt":"2023-03-06T21:52:17","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/icarusmedical.com\/?p=5575"},"modified":"2023-03-06T16:52:20","modified_gmt":"2023-03-06T21:52:20","slug":"the-best-knee-brace-for-a-meniscus-tear","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/icarusmedical.com\/blog\/the-best-knee-brace-for-a-meniscus-tear\/","title":{"rendered":"The Best Knee Brace for a Meniscus Tear"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-post\" data-elementor-id=\"5575\" class=\"elementor elementor-5575\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-section-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-48b94ff e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"48b94ff\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2f5c737 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"2f5c737\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c7c9126 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"c7c9126\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">What is a Meniscus Tear?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d9ff86a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"d9ff86a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A meniscus tear is one of the most common knee injuries, <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ucsfhealth.org\/en\/conditions\/meniscus-tear\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">affecting approximately 1 million people in the U.S. each year<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, regardless of age or fitness level. If you&#8217;ve suffered a meniscus tear or injury, your physician may advise wearing a knee brace as part of your treatment plan. The best knee brace for a meniscus tear will offer both support and protection for the meniscus, safeguarding it against any excessive force or pressure that could potentially worsen the injury.\u00a0<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A meniscus tear is an injury to <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/icarusmedical.com\/blog\/what-is-cartilage-its-function\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">the cartilage in the knee joint<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> that provides cushioning and stability to the knee. A meniscus tear can occur in several ways, including twisting the knee with excessive force or overextending it. The symptoms of a meniscus tear may include severe knee pain, inflammation, and difficulty in bending the knee. As with any knee injury, the treatment plan can vary from person to person. The recovery journey, depending on the tear\u2019s magnitude, may involve physical therapy, pain management medication, and in severe cases, surgical intervention.<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are <\/span><b>two types<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> of meniscus tears. <\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bcc3d15 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"bcc3d15\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-31cec5b elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"31cec5b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-medium\">Acute Tears<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5e6a2fc e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"5e6a2fc\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e532f17 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e532f17\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Acute knee tears are frequently caused by sudden trauma during physical activity. When the knee is over-extended or twisted too quickly, an acute tear can occur. Oftentime acute tears happen in conjunction with other injuries, particularly anterior cruciate ligament (ACL) tears. The extent of the tear will dictate the treatment required, with many acute tears requiring surgical intervention.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-575f28a e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"575f28a\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8938ea1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8938ea1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-medium\">Degenerative Tears<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5550268 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"5550268\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c474a6b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c474a6b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Degenerative tears, in contrast to acute tears, deteriorate and intensify over time. This type of tear is a result of the gradual wear and tear of the hyaline cartilage and meniscus, which can take several years to manifest as knee pain. Unfortunately, most degenerative meniscus tears are not diagnosed until the damage has reached a point of significant discomfort. Unlike acute tears, surgery is not always necessary for degenerative tears.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d3e16c2 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"d3e16c2\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bace81c elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"bace81c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Types of Knee Braces for a Meniscus Tear<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-83fc249 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"83fc249\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-fb90b51 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"fb90b51\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Depending on the injury, surgery might be necessary in order to repair the meniscus or remove the torn portion. In either case, it is likely that your doctor will recommend a supportive knee brace to protect and stabilize the injured meniscus depending on the extent of your injury.<br \/><br \/><\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The type of knee brace you should wear for a meniscus tear depends on the extent of your injury and where you are in the recovery process. Listed below are some common types of knee braces for a meniscus tear:<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-fcd1ca2 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"fcd1ca2\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-65b4aa8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"65b4aa8\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-medium\">Stabilizing Knee Brace<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d936401 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"d936401\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-97d2ba2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"97d2ba2\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A stabilizing knee brace provides substantial stability and support to the knee and is often recommended for the early stages of recovery after a meniscus tear.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b749569 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"b749569\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d3f8e2e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"d3f8e2e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-medium\">Compression Knee Sleeve<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3de2a25 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"3de2a25\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ac48cf3 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ac48cf3\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A compression knee sleeve is designed to provide compression to the knee in order to reduce swelling and pain. Compression knee sleeves are a great option for individuals looking to still stay active and engaged in physical activity while wearing a brace.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5a33c7a e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"5a33c7a\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a0b5b5c elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a0b5b5c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-medium\">Hinged Knee Brace<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5cd1d06 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"5cd1d06\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d6a415c elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"d6a415c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A hinged knee brace provides additional support and stability to the knee and may be recommended for moderate to severe meniscus tears. <\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2fae92c e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"2fae92c\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-aff51db elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"aff51db\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-medium\">Unloader Knee Brace<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f3afb15 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"f3afb15\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-845b093 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"845b093\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An unloader brace is another great option for patients suffering from a meniscus tear, especially for those who also have osteoarthritis in addition to their meniscus injury. An unloader brace is designed to redistribute the weight bearing load away from the impacted area of the knee and onto the brace frame, which can help to reduce pain and increase mobility.<br \/><br \/>As for any other injury or illness, it is important to consult with a doctor or physical therapist to determine the best form of treatment for you.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-60bf319 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"60bf319\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-63aaec6 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"63aaec6\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Takeaways<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-52d8c43 e-con-boxed e-con\" data-id=\"52d8c43\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;content_width&quot;:&quot;boxed&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-21d6d0a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"21d6d0a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If an unloader Brace sounds right for you, then look no further than the <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/icarusmedical.com\/icarus-products\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Icarus Medical Ascender knee brace<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Through the use of 3D scans, 3D models, and 3D printing, Icarus Medical designs custom knee braces tailored to alleviate and target your pain directly. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Ascender<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> knee brace can provide those suffering from a meniscus tear with additional support and stabilization. By transferring pressure from the knee joint to the brace frame, the Ascender knee brace helps alleviate stress and reduces the risk of knee pain, osteoarthritis, and other knee injuries.\u00a0<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Icarus Medical, we offer a one-of-a-kind tension dialing system, allowing you to customize the level of support you receive from your brace whenever you want. Whether you&#8217;re in the early stages of recovery fro